 "html": "<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">I'm always a little cautious about baking bread. &nbsp;But I think I overcame that fear today. &nbsp;I baked a perfect ciabatta and it was so easy that even a child &nbsp;could do it. Delicious with thick butter or just as a scrap to mop up gravy with. &nbsp;You'll need a Kenwood or an electric mixer. &nbsp;The secret lies in the whisking, because the gluten needs to develop. &nbsp;Don't panic if the dough looks sloppy &nbsp;&#8211; that's how it's meant to look.</p>\n\n\n<div data-recipe-slot=\"1\"></div>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-038.jpg\"><img src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-038-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"ciabatta 038\" class=\"wp-image-1416\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>",
