   {
    "title": null,
    "items": [
     "500g cake flour<br><img src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-001-300x225.jpg\" title=\"ciabatta-001\" alt class=\"direction-step-image\" loading=\"lazy\">",
     "500 ml lukewarm water<br>",
     "1 packet (10g) instant yeast<br><img src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-005-225x300.jpg\" title=\"ciabatta-005\" alt class=\"direction-step-image\" loading=\"lazy\">",
     "5 ml salt",
     "10 ml sugar"
    ]
   }
  ],
  "directionsTitle": "Method",
  "directionGroups": [
   {
    "title": null,
    "steps": [
     "Preheat your oven to 220 degrees Celsius.",
     "Put all your ingredients in your Kenwood bowl.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-008.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"ciabatta-008\">",
     "Beat with the K-beater for 12 minutes &#8211; stay by the mixer because it really dances around.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-014.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"ciabatta-014\">",
     "Cover with cling wrap and let rise until double the volume (about 45 minutes).<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-022.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-022.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"ciabatta 022\" title=\"Ciabatta - met dik botter\"></a>",
     "Spray a baking tray with spray and cook and sprinkle a thick layer of flour over it.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-010.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-010.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"ciabatta 010\" title=\"Ciabatta - met dik botter\"></a>",
     "Scrape the dough out onto the tray with a dough scraper &#8211; shape it into an oval loaf.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-025.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-025.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"ciabatta 025\" title=\"Ciabatta - met dik botter\"></a>",
     "Put it in the oven and also put a bowl of cold water in the oven &#8211; it makes the crust nice and crisp.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-028.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-028.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"ciabatta 028\" title=\"Ciabatta - met dik botter\"></a>",
     "Bake for 20 to 30 minutes  &#8211; keep an eye on it until it sounds hollow when you tap it and is nicely browned.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-035.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-035.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"ciabatta 035\" title=\"Ciabatta - met dik botter\"></a>",
     "Now eat the bread with thick butter or drag it through gravy.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-0451.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/ciabatta-0451.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"ciabatta 045\" title=\"Ciabatta - met dik botter\"></a>"
